---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Marketing Apps for Corporate Gifting in 2026';
const description = 'Compare Shopify email apps for corporate gifting, account-based outreach, bulk orders, recipient communication, and repeat business.';
const apps = [['Klaviyo','Corporate gifting with account data','Useful for account, purchaser, recipient, order, and engagement segmentation.','B2B identity and recipient permissions need careful governance.','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/segmentation'],['Omnisend','Gift businesses coordinating commerce campaigns','A practical fit for seasonal, order, and recipient journeys.','Bulk-order and reward logic need testing.','https://www.omnisend.com/features/'],['Sequenzy','Boutique corporate-gifting teams','Good for quote nurture, order education, and recipient follow-up.','Account and bulk-order integrations should be confirmed.','https://sequenzy.com/'],['Brevo','B2B and transactional operations','Useful for account communication, campaigns, and operational updates.','Traffic separation and privacy rules require care.','https://www.brevo.com/features/transactional-email/'],['Shopify Email','Small gifting operations','A simple option for account announcements and seasonal guides.','Less suited to account-level branching.','https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing']];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email marketing apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">Corporate gifting has more than one buyer and more than one delivery moment. The program must distinguish the account, purchaser, recipient, and operational owner.</p><p>Measure qualified account inquiries, repeat business, bulk-order margin, delivery success, and support. Keep recipient marketing permission separate from an order’s operational contact, and make invoicing, shipping, and gift messaging clear.</p><h2>Shortlist at a glance</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>Strength</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[2]}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for corporate gifting</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[2]}</p><p><strong>Why it stands out:</strong> {a[0]} is useful when account and recipient states remain distinct and the workflow can support quote, order, delivery, and renewal or repeat-gifting moments. Give account buyers a clear owner and keep recipient communication appropriately limited. Corporate gifting is a relationship and operations problem, not only a seasonal campaign.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros</th><td>{a[2]}</td></tr><tr><th>Cons</th><td>{a[3]}</td></tr><tr><th>Pricing context</th><td>Review current contacts, sends, transactional, automation, and B2B integration costs; account and recipient data can increase scope.</td></tr><tr><th>Source</th><td><a href={a[4]} rel="nofollow">Official product information</a></td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Need</th><th>Prioritize</th><th>Measure</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Account clarity</td><td>Buyer and recipient identity</td><td>Qualified account conversion</td></tr><tr><td>Operations</td><td>Bulk-order and delivery state</td><td>Delivery success</td></tr><tr><td>Retention</td><td>Repeat-gifting follow-up</td><td>Account retention</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Explore <a href="/alternatives">Shopify alternatives</a>, review <a href="/for/b2b-wholesale">B2B use cases</a>, or browse <a href="/apps">all Shopify email apps</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
